AboutMe:
I'm a chemical engineer by training (graduated with my PhD in Dec 2014), working at a solar cell factory as a Device Process Engineer. I do a lot of programming to collect and analyze data, as well as setting up hardware, including the physical setup as well as the programming to run equipment and store/process/analyze the data.

I work on quantitative finance while not at my job, and am nearly finished with a data downloader for historical data from interactive brokers.

I also work on building devices, such as a dust concentration monitor that I'm working on now.

My hobbies include biking, music (drumming, bass, and guitar), surfing, hiking, and working with plants.
